--mvc crud with thymeleaf--

1.create spring starter project

2.boot 2.0.4, java10

3.project dependencies - web, thymeleaf and MySql

4.application properties
	only database config needed, not need of view resolver for thymeleaf

5.create static and template files

6.create database in mysql

7.forgot to add dependence jpa, 
	right click on pom
	select spring
	edit starters
	select jpa

8.important
	to make thymeleaf to find controllers , package name must be important
	eg : 
	spring boot app package name is com.example.demo
	then, controller package name must be com.example.demo.controller

9.Note : by default , CrudRepository methods by default transaction enabled, no need to handle transaction.


